Steps to run osgi on MS server
1) On MS:
	a) mserverctl manual; mserverctl stop 
	b) disable mscomponent on MS
    	vi ~/mscomponent/bin/_disable_mscomponent.rc
    	disable_mscomponent=true
    	disableAppServerAgent=false
	c) mserverctl start
	d) devappctl stop

2)	copy jre in "/data"

3)	Download the build from Hudson (http://kali.barco.com:8080/job/silsvn01%20nimbus%20OSGi/), then on MS: 
	a.	mkdir com.barco.nimbus.equinox.product
	b.	cp downloaded zip in above dir
	c.	Unzip - *.zip
	d.	rm –rf *.zip
	
4) cd /data1/jre/lib/i386, create the below links
	ln -s libnio.so libgio-2.0.so.0
	ln -s libnio.so libgobject-2.0.so.0
	
5) create a new collection "nimbus.default.licenselist" in the db

6)	Then, cd /data and create a shell script runOSGi.sh with following content
	export BLM_DYNAMIC_DIR=/data/license
	export BLM_LICENSE_FILE=/data/license/nimbus.lic	
/data/jre/bin/java -Declipse.ignoreApp=true -Dosgi.noShutdown=true -Dorg.osgi.service.http.port=9090 -Dorg.eclipse.equinox.http.jetty.autostart=true -Dbundles.configuration.location=/data/com.barco.nimbus.equinox.product/configuration -jar /data/com.barco.nimbus.equinox.product/plugins/org.eclipse.equinox.launcher_1.3.0.v20130327-1440.jar > /data/mrapp.log

7) sh runOSGi.sh - logs will be printed in /data/mrapp.log


